<span id="v.iv.vi.xiv-p9"></span> This vindication of these terms of the
apostle from *Docetism* is important. The word which our A.V. has
translated *sinful* is a stronger term in the original. It is not the
adjective <span class="Greek"><span
id="v.iv.vi.xiv-p9.1"></span>ἁμαρτωλοῦ</span>, but the substantive <span
class="Greek"><span id="v.iv.vi.xiv-p9.2"></span>ἁμαρτίας</span>,
amounting to “flesh of sin,” *i.e.* (as Dean Alford interprets it) “the
flesh whose attribute and character is *sin*.” “The words <span
